        <!-- ========== USAGE ========== -->
        <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display:none;padding-top:32px;">
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Date Picker is designed for calendar date selection via a text input and popover.</p>
            <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:24px;margin-top:24px;">
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>When to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">When users must select a specific calendar date (date of birth, due date, appointment).</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">When users must select a span of dates (report range, booking, date filter) &rarr; use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">type="range"</code>.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">When presets (Today, Last 7 days, This month) cover the majority of cases &rarr; enable <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">showPresets</code>.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;">When the selection must be confirmed before applying (filters, batch ops) &rarr; enable <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">showFooter</code>.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div style="padding:24px;background:var(--prism-surface);border:1px solid var(--prism-border);border-radius:12px;">
                <h3 style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--prism-text);margin-bottom:16px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>When NOT to use</h3>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border:none;background:transparent;padding-left:20px;font-size:14.5px;">
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">For single-day recurring selection (day-of-week) &mdash; use Checkbox Group or Radio Group.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">For date + time input &mdash; use a DateTime Picker (Date Picker + time input).</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;margin-bottom:8px;">For free-form text dates in prose &mdash; use a plain Text Input.</li>
                  <li style="border:none;background:transparent;">For scheduling multiple discrete dates &mdash; use a multi-date calendar pattern.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="single-vs-range" class="doc-section-title">Single vs Range</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Pick the Type axis based on the selection model required.</p>
            <table class="size-table">
              <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Behaviour</th><th>When to pick</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td><code>single</code></td><td>One input, one calendar. Selecting a day commits immediately (or stages if <code>showFooter</code>).</td><td>DOB, appointment, due date, scheduling.</td></tr>
                <tr><td><code>range</code></td><td>Two inputs (start, end) + dual calendar. First click = start; second click = end. Days between render a range highlight.</td><td>Report period, booking, filtering records between dates.</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="presets-vs-manual" class="doc-section-title">Presets vs Manual Entry</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Presets short-circuit common date spans. Keep manual entry available for everything else.</p>
            <ul class="doc-list">
              <li><strong>Surface presets</strong> when &ge; 60% of users pick one of them (Today, Last 7 days, This month). They reduce clicks to one.</li>
              <li><strong>Always keep manual day-grid selection available</strong> &mdash; presets are shortcuts, not replacements.</li>
              <li><strong>Keep presets concise</strong> &mdash; a long list clutters the popover and increases scan time.</li>
              <li><strong>Allow custom presets</strong> via the <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">presets</code> prop (e.g. "This quarter", "Year to date") when the domain calls for it.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Complete Do's and Don'ts</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Guidelines for effective Date Picker usage.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Range for spans:</strong> Use <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">type="range"</code> when start and end dates are both required.</li>
                <li><strong>Surface presets:</strong> Offer Today, Last 7 / 30 days, This month for common spans.</li>
                <li><strong>Staged commit:</strong> Enable <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">showFooter</code> for expensive operations (report, query).</li>
                <li><strong>Respect bounds:</strong> Disable invalid days in the grid &mdash; don't error only on apply.</li>
                <li><strong>Mirror for RTL:</strong> Mirror the weekday row and grid order, not just the input.</li>
                <li><strong>Locale-aware format:</strong> <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">DD/MM/YYYY</code> for APAC/EU, <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">MM/DD/YYYY</code> for en-US.</li>
                <li><strong>Close after commit:</strong> Close the popover after Apply (or after single-click select without Footer).</li>
                <li><strong>Announce selection:</strong> Read the selected date via <code style="font-family:monospace;font-size:13px;padding:2px 8px;border-radius:6px;background:rgba(37,99,235,0.06);color:var(--prism-violet);">aria-live</code> for screen readers.</li>
              </ul></div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span><ul>
                <li><strong>Two Single pickers:</strong> Don't use two independent Single pickers for a range &mdash; they can't enforce end &ge; start.</li>
                <li><strong>Hide frequent presets:</strong> Don't tuck popular presets behind "Custom" when most users need them.</li>
                <li><strong>Footer on inline forms:</strong> Don't gate immediate-commit form fields behind an Apply button.</li>
                <li><strong>Errors only on submit:</strong> Don't let users pick an invalid date and reject it only at form time.</li>
                <li><strong>Half-RTL:</strong> Don't flip only the input without mirroring the calendar grid.</li>
                <li><strong>Hard-coded format:</strong> Don't force one format globally &mdash; respect locale.</li>
                <li><strong>Leave popover open:</strong> Don't keep the popover open after Apply &mdash; the user has moved on.</li>
                <li><strong>Visual-only highlight:</strong> Don't rely on visual selection alone &mdash; non-sighted users won't know.</li>
              </ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <hr class="doc-divider"/>

          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="related" class="doc-section-title">Related</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used instead of Date Picker.</p>
            <div class="related-grid">
              <a href="Calendar.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="4" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M16 2v4M8 2v4M3 10h18"/></svg> Calendar</a>
